%% RHOAI 3.3 Platform Data Flows
%% Generated by Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy) 443/TCP
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuthIDP as OAuth/OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HTTPRoute as HTTPRoute
    participant KRBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Runtime as Serving Runtime<br/>(vLLM/OVMS/MLServer)<br/>8000-8080/TCP
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>(S3/PVC/HuggingFace)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: Model Inference (End-to-End)

    Client->>Router: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Gateway: Forward<br/>HTTPS/443
    Gateway->>AuthProxy: ext_authz check<br/>HTTPS/8443 (service-CA)
    AuthProxy->>OAuthIDP: Token validation<br/>HTTPS/443
    OAuthIDP-->>AuthProxy: Auth response
    AuthProxy-->>Gateway: Auth decision + user info
    Gateway->>HTTPRoute: Route match<br/>Lua filter injects Bearer token
    HTTPRoute->>KRBACProxy: Forward (optional)<br/>HTTPS/8443
    KRBACProxy->>Runtime: Inference request<br/>HTTP/8000-8080
    Runtime->>Storage: Load model weights<br/>HTTPS/443 or PVC mount
    Storage-->>Runtime: Model artifacts
    Runtime-->>KRBACProxy: Inference response (JSON/SSE)
    KRBACProxy-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Router: Response (Bearer stripped by Lua)
    Router-->>Client: JSON/SSE Response

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 2: AI Pipeline Execution

    participant PipeAPI as ds-pipeline API<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as Database<br/>(MySQL/PostgreSQL)
    participant ArgoCtrl as Argo Controller<br/>2746/TCP HTTPS
    participant MLMD2 as ML Metadata<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant ObjStore as Object Storage<br/>(S3/MinIO)

    Client->>PipeAPI: Create PipelineRun<br/>HTTP/8888
    PipeAPI->>DB: Persist pipeline<br/>TCP/3306 or 5432
    PipeAPI->>ArgoCtrl: Create Workflow CR
    ArgoCtrl->>ArgoCtrl: Create step Pods
    ArgoCtrl->>MLMD2: Log artifacts<br/>gRPC/8080
    ArgoCtrl->>ObjStore: Store artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443
    ArgoCtrl-->>PipeAPI: Status updates
    PipeAPI-->>Client: Pipeline status

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 3: Model Training (TrainJob)

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrainerCtrl as Trainer Controller
    participant JobSet as JobSet Controller
    participant TrainPods as Training Pods<br/>29500+/TCP

    Client->>K8sAPI: Create TrainJob CR<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI->>TrainerCtrl: Webhook validation<br/>9443/TCP
    TrainerCtrl->>JobSet: Create JobSet CR
    JobSet->>TrainPods: Create training Pods
    TrainerCtrl->>TrainerCtrl: Create NetworkPolicy
    TrainPods->>TrainPods: NCCL/MPI communication<br/>TCP/29500+
    TrainPods-->>TrainerCtrl: Training metrics<br/>HTTP/28080
    TrainerCtrl->>K8sAPI: Update TrainJob status

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 4: Guardrails Safety Check

    participant VllmGW as vllm-orchestrator-gw<br/>8090/TCP HTTP
    participant GuardOrch as Guardrails Orchestrator<br/>8033/TCP HTTP
    participant Detectors as Detectors<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant LLMBackend as LLM Backend<br/>(vLLM)

    Client->>VllmGW: Chat completion<br/>HTTP/8090
    VllmGW->>GuardOrch: Forward with detector specs<br/>HTTP/8033
    GuardOrch->>Detectors: Input scan<br/>HTTP/8080
    Detectors-->>GuardOrch: Detection results
    GuardOrch->>LLMBackend: LLM inference
    LLMBackend-->>GuardOrch: LLM response
    GuardOrch->>Detectors: Output scan<br/>HTTP/8080
    Detectors-->>GuardOrch: Detection results
    GuardOrch-->>VllmGW: Filtered response
    VllmGW-->>Client: Safe response
